The paper discusses location privacy, which is a topic commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and database (cs.DB) communities. The paper also discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of noise generation mechanisms, which is a topic commonly studied in the signal processing (cs.SI) community.
